[SN]TITLE[SN]
Halloween warm weather: Your pictures

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
This year's Halloween is the warmest on record in the UK, BBC weather has confirmed.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
BBC News website readers have been sending us their pictures from around the UK.
The day started with clear skies in many parts of the UK. Simon Baker Cooke posted this early morning photo on Twitter as the sun rose over Glastonbury Tor.
Terry Musgove is spending a long weekend in Whitby, North Yorkshire. He sent us the panoramic view he woke up to this morning.
In Somerset, the autumnal colours were captured by Graham George as he looked out into his garden in Enmore.
Mike Hilton took this picture of his dog Betty enjoying the sunrise on Sandbanks beach, in Dorset.
Jeremy Gahagan, in London, usually wears flip-flops throughout the summer, and was surprised to be walking around in them on Halloween.
In preparation for a day of trick or treats, Damien Davies dressed up his one-week-old son, Harrison Stanley, for his very first Halloween.
Amanda Park took her grand-daughter, Olivia, to a very sunny Alder Carr Farm in Suffolk to pick out pumpkins.
Liam Rushton sent this picture taken outside his house in Stevenage, Hertfordshire, which he titled "one hot Halloween".
Tony Berndes spent the day making the most of the sun on the beach in Bude in Cornwall.
